Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
editResize(25.10)                                            editResize(25.10)

Name
       editResize - Resizes wires, bus guides, and pins

Syntax
       editResize

       [-help]

       [-keep_center_line {0 1 auto}] [-no_conn]

       [-polygon_edge_start {<x y>} | -to <float_value>]

       {[[[-direction  {x  y  diag45  diag135}  -side  {high  low}]  | [-poly-
       gon_edge_start {x y} -polygon_edge_end {<x y>}]] [-offset <float_value>
       | -to <float_value>]] | [-corner {low_left low_right up_left  up_right}
       -dx <float_value> -dy <float_value>]}

       Resizes wires, bus guides, and pins. The editResize command can be used
       to:

              * Change the length of wires and bus guides.

              * Change the width of wires and bus guides.

              * Enlarge  or shrink wires by changing both the length and width
                of a wire simultaneously.

              * Change the width of physical pins.

       While changing the wire width to fix EM violations, apply the following
       setting before invoking the editResize command:

       setEditMode -unrestricted_regular_wire_width true

       By default, when you are changing the width of a wire, it snaps to  the
       closest  non-default  route  (NDR)  available.  If  you  set the -unre-
       stricted_regular_wire_width parameter to true, a wire can be  stretched
       to any width without any restrictions.

       Typically, the editResize command can be used in two modes:

       Mode  1  -  Change the size of a wire or pin in only one direction at a
       time

       If -direction is specified, the tool changes the size in the  specified
       direction only. In this mode, the editResize command can be used to:

              * Change  the  length  of  selected regular and special wires by
                stretching or shrinking them and then  snapping  them  to  the
                closest  manufacturing grid point. The editResize command also
                supports the stretching/shrinking of 45 and 135-degree wires.

                Note: Use the editSelect command to select the wires.

              *

                Change the width of selected wires and update  vias  connected
                to the changed wires to maintain the via-to-wire dimension ra-
                tio.  editResize can be used to change the width of regular as
                well as special wires:

                * For regular wires, if the width value you specified  is  not
                  defined  in  the  tech  LEF, the tool snaps the width of the
                  regular wire to the closest value defined in the default  or
                  non-default rule and prints the following message in the log
                  file:

                  WARNING: The wire width is not defined in default or non de-
                  fault  rule, snap wire width to the closest value defined in
                  LEF file

                  The tool also selects a suitable via  cell  defined  in  the
                  tech  LEF file. If a suitable via cell is not available, the
                  tool does not drop any via.

                  When you change the width of a regular wire, the center line
                  is still connected with  the  neighboring  wires  after  the
                  change:

                * For  a special wire, you can change the wire width freely by
                  specifying an incremental value. The  tool  uses  viagen  to
                  generate a via after the width change of a special wire.

              Note: Use the editSelect command to select the wires.

              If  you  change  the width of a wire, and then change it back to
              the original width, you might see a discrepancy due to rounding.

              Note: If you specify a width value that is not an even  multiple
              of  the  manufacturing grid value, the software displays a warn-
              ing.

              * Resize patch wires. Patch wires can be stretched in  four  di-
                rections:

              *

                Change  the width of physical pins. While using the editResize
                command to change the pin width, keep the following points  in
                mind:

              *

                * If  setEditMode -drc_on true has been specified before modi-
                  fying the pin width, the tool follows the rules from the LEF
                  file while changing pin width.

                * The pin width, whether vertical or horizontal, should not be
                  less than the minimum width defined in the LEF file.

                * If you specify a value less than minimum width  for  a  pin,
                  the tool uses the minimum width for that pin.

       Mode  2  - Change the size of a wire in both the x and y directions si-
       multaneously

       If -direction is not specified, the tool changes  both  the  width  and
       height  of  the  selected wire at the same time. You can use -corner to
       specify the start corner from which to stretch or shrink the wire. This
       mode works for only horizontal or vertical special wires in the no_con-
       nection (-no_conn) mode. Use -dx and -dy to  specify  the  distance  to
       stretch the wire in x and y directions, respectively.

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description that includes type and default infor-
              mation for each editResize parameter. For a detailed description
              of the command, use the man command:

              man editResize

       -corner {low_left low_right up_left up_right}
              Specifies  the  starting  corner  from  which the wire should be
              stretched.

       -direction {x y diag45 diag135}
              Specifies the direction in which  the  wire  or  pin  is  to  be
              stretched or shrunk:

              * x - Resizes wires or pins horizontally. For a horizontal wire,
                specify the direction as x if you want to modify the length of
                the  wire  (i.e  stretch or shrink the horizontal wire). For a
                vertical wire, specify the direction as x if you want to  mod-
                ify the width of the wire.

              * y  -  Resizes wires or pins vertically. For a horizontal wire,
                specify the direction as y if you want to modify the width  of
                the  wire.  For a vertical wire, specify the direction as y if
                you want to modify the length of the  wire   (i.e  stretch  or
                shrink the vertical wire).

              * diag45 - Resizes the selected wires in the 45-degree direction
                by the specified offset value.

                Note: This parameter can be used only for wires.

              * diag135  - Resizes the selected wires in the 135-degree direc-
                tion by the specified offset value.

                Note: This parameter can be used only for wires.

       -dx <float_value>
              Specifies the distance to which the wire should be stretched  in
              the x direction.

       -dy <float_value>
              Specifies  the distance to which the wire should be stretched in
              the y direction.

       -keep_center_line {0 1 auto}
              Controls whether the wire or physical pin is  resized  with  the
              center line unchanged:

              * 0 - Resizes the wire or pin from the specified side only. This
                option   works   in  both  the  connection  and  no_connection
                (-no_conn) modes.

                This setting cannot be used for changing the width  of  signal
                wires.

              * 1  - Resizes the wire or pin from both the low and high sides,
                even if you are stretching it from only one side. This is done
                to keep the center line unchanged.

                This option works in both  the  connection  and  no_connection
                (-no_conn)  modes  for wires. However, a physical pin can keep
                the center line unchanged during a resize in the no-connection
                mode only.

              * auto - When set to auto, the  software  automatically  detects
                when to keep the center line unchanged.

              Default: auto

       -no_conn
              Resizes  the  wire without auto via/wire creation and DRC check-
              ing.

              If -no_conn is not specified, the tool will  reprocess  the  via
              and do basic DRC checking:

              Note: Patch wires are resized without auto via/wire creation and
              DRC checking even if -no_conn is not specified.

       -offset <float_value>
              Specifies,  in  microns, the distance to which the wires or pins
              should be stretched or shrunk.

       -polygon_edge_end {<x y>}
              Specifies the end point for a polygon edge {x y}. This option is
              used only to resize a polygon.

       -polygon_edge_start {<x y>}
              Specifies the start point for a polygon edge {x y}. This  option
              is used only to resize a polygon.

       -side {high low}
              Specifies the side from which the wire or pin is to be stretched
              or shrunk:

              * high  - Stretches or shrinks wires or pins from the top or the
                right.

              * low - Stretches or shrinks the wires or pins from  the  bottom
                or the left.

       -to <float_value>
              Specifies,  in  microns,  the new height for selected horizontal
              wires or the new width for selected vertical wires.

Examples
              * The following command stretches  the  selected  vertical  wire
                from the top by 8.5 <mu>m.

                editResize -direction y -offset 8.5 -side high

              * The  following  command  stretches  the selected vertical wire
                from the bottom by 0.511 <mu>m.

                editResize -direction y -offset -0.511 -side low

              * The following command shrinks the selected vertical wire  from
                the bottom by 0.619 <mu>m.

                editResize -direction y -offset 0.619 -side low

              * The  following  command stretches the selected horizontal wire
                from the right by 1.27 <mu>m.

                editResize -direction x -offset 1.27 -side high

              * The following command shrinks a horizontal wire from the  left
                by 0.443 <mu>m.

                editResize -direction x -offset 0.443 -side low

              * The  following  command  stretches  a horizontal wire from the
                left by 0.86 <mu>m.

                editResize -direction x -offset -0.86 -side low

              * The following command increases the width of the selected hor-
                izontal special wire by 0.01 <mu>m:

                editResize -direction y -offset 0.01 -side high

              * The following command changes the width of the selected  hori-
                zontal regular wire to  0.48 <mu>m:

                editResize -to 0.48 -direction y -side high

                If 0.48 is not defined in the NDR, the tool snaps the width to
                the closest value defined in the NDR.

              * The  following command increases the vertical width of the se-
                lected physical pin by 3 <mu>m each from both top and  bottom,
                keeping the center line unchanged:

                editResize   -direction   y  -offset  3  -side  high  -no_conn
                -keep_center_line 1

              * The following command reduces the horizontal width of the  se-
                lected  physical pin by 3 <mu>m each from both left and right,
                keeping the center line unchanged:

                editResize  -direction  x  -offset  -3  -side   low   -no_conn
                -keep_center_line 1

